Goldman Sachs Group Inc. Buys 181,819 Shares of Atlassian Corporation PLC (TEAM)


					Posted by Chloe McGuire on Jul 24th, 2017 // No Comments




Goldman Sachs Group Inc. increased its stake in  Atlassian Corporation PLC (NASDAQ:TEAM) by 575.6% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The firm owned 213,407 shares of the technology company’s stock after buying an additional 181,819 shares during the period. Goldman Sachs Group Inc. owned approximately 0.09% of Atlassian Corporation PLC worth $6,391,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
A number of other large investors also recently modified their holdings of TEAM. Wellington Management Group LLP increased its position in  Atlassian Corporation PLC by 1,316.3% in the first quarter. Wellington Management Group LLP now owns 4,188,567 shares of the technology company’s stock worth $125,448,000 after buying an additional 3,892,824 shares during the last quarter.  FMR LLC increased its position in  Atlassian Corporation PLC by 354.8% in the first quarter. FMR LLC now owns 2,189,836 shares of the technology company’s stock worth $65,586,000 after buying an additional 1,708,347 shares during the last quarter.  Artisan Partners Limited Partnership increased its position in  Atlassian Corporation PLC by 16.8% in the first quarter. Artisan Partners Limited Partnership now owns 6,017,450 shares of the technology company’s stock worth $180,223,000 after buying an additional 866,132 shares during the last quarter.  Baillie Gifford & Co. increased its position in  Atlassian Corporation PLC by 6.8% in the first quarter. Baillie Gifford & Co. now owns 10,793,259 shares of the technology company’s stock worth $323,259,000 after buying an additional 682,668 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, Norges Bank acquired a new position in  Atlassian Corporation PLC during the fourth quarter worth approximately $10,176,000. Institutional investors own  81.62% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Atlassian Corporation PLC alerts:



Shares of Atlassian Corporation PLC (NASDAQ:TEAM) opened at 35.75 on Monday. The firm’s market capitalization is $8.06 billion. The company has a 50 day moving average price of $35.53 and a 200-day moving average price of $31.80. Atlassian Corporation PLC has a 12 month low of $23.80 and a 12 month high of $37.90. 





Atlassian Corporation PLC (NASDAQ:TEAM) last announced its quarterly earnings data on Thursday, April 27th. The technology company reported ($0.05) earnings per share for the quarter, beating the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of ($0.10) by $0.05. The firm had revenue of $159.90 million during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $156.64 million. Atlassian Corporation PLC had a negative return on equity of 1.74% and a negative net margin of 4.62%. Atlassian Corporation PLC’s quarterly revenue was up 35.6% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period in the previous year, the company earned $0.07 earnings per share.  Equities research analysts expect that  Atlassian Corporation PLC will post $0.33 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION WARNING: This report was first  posted by Chaffey Breeze and is the property of of Chaffey Breeze. If you are reading this report on another publication, it was illegally copied and reposted in violation of international trademark and copyright law. The original version of this report can be read at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/24/goldman-sachs-group-inc-buys-181819-shares-of-atlassian-corporation-plc-team.html. 
A number of research analysts have recently commented on the company. Zacks Investment Research downgraded Atlassian Corporation PLC from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Friday. BMO Capital Markets increased their price objective on Atlassian Corporation PLC from $33.00 to $40.00 and gave the company a “market perform” rating in a report on Friday, July 7th. Jefferies Group LLC  reiterated a “buy” rating and issued a $41.00 price objective on shares of Atlassian Corporation PLC in a report on Friday, June 2nd. ValuEngine upgraded Atlassian Corporation PLC from a “sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Friday, June 2nd. Finally, Oppenheimer Holdings, Inc.  reiterated an “outperform” rating and issued a $40.00 price objective (up previously from $35.00) on shares of Atlassian Corporation PLC in a report on Monday, May 1st. Seven equities research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and nine have given a buy rating to the company’s stock. The stock presently has a consensus rating of “Buy” and a consensus target price of $36.09.
Atlassian Corporation PLC Company Profile
Atlassian Corporation Plc is a holding company. The Company offers a range of team collaboration products. The Company offers products, including JIRA, Confluence, HipChat, Bitbucket and JIRA Service Desk, for software developers, information technology (IT) managers and knowledge workers. The Company offers JIRA for team planning and project management; Confluence for team content creation and sharing; HipChat for team real-time messaging and communications; Bitbucket for team code sharing and management, and JIRA Service Desk for team service and support applications.







